@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home Page";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
        margin: 0;
        background: #f5f5f5;
      }
      
      .hero {
        height: 400px;
        background: linear-gradient(rgba(0,0,0,0.5), rgba(0,0,0,0.5)), url('img/background.jpeg');
        background-size: cover;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        color: white;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .hero h1 {
        font-size: 4em;
        text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
      }

      .content {
        max-width: 1000px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 20px;
      }

      .card-container {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
        gap: 20px;
        margin-top: 20px;
      }

      .card {
        background: white;
        border-radius: 10px;
        overflow: hidden;
        box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        transition: transform 0.3s;
      }

      .card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-5px);
      }

      .card img {
        width: 100%;
        height: 200px;
        object-fit: cover;
      }

      .card-content {
        padding: 20px;
      }

      .stats {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-around;
        background: #f8f9fa;
        padding: 20px;
        margin: 20px 0;
        border-radius: 10px;
      }

      .stat {
        text-align: center;
      }

      .stat-number {
        font-size: 2em;
        font-weight: bold;
        color: #dc143c;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Discover Japan<br>日本を発見しよう</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="content">
      <div class="stats">
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-number">47</div>
          <div>Prefectures</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-number">125M</div>
          <div>Population</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-number">6,852</div>
          <div>Islands</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card-container">
        <div class="card">
          <img src="img/fuji.jpeg" alt="Mount Fuji">
          <div class="card-content">
            <h2>Mount Fuji</h2>
            <p>Mount Fuji, Japan's most sacred mountain, rises 3,776 meters above sea level. This active stratovolcano last erupted in 1707 and has been a UNESCO World 
              Heritage site since 2013. Its perfect conical shape, snow-capped peak, and cultural significance have made it a symbol of Japan and a popular destination for 
              climbers and photographers alike. The mountain is visible from Tokyo on clear days and attracts over 200,000 climbers annually during its summer climbing season.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <img src="img/tokyo.jpeg" alt="Tokyo">
          <div class="card-content">
            <h2>Tokyo</h2>
            <p>Tokyo, Japan's bustling capital, seamlessly blends ultramodern and traditional elements. Home to over 37 million people in its metropolitan area, it features 
              cutting-edge technology, world-class dining, and vibrant pop culture. From the historic Senso-ji Temple to the futuristic Shibuya Crossing, Tokyo offers 
              countless attractions. The city's efficient train system, diverse neighborhoods like Harajuku and Akihabara, and status as the world's largest urban economy 
              make it a global powerhouse of culture and commerce.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <img src="img/kyoto.jpeg" alt="Kyoto">
          <div class="card-content">
            <h2>Kyoto</h2>
            <p>Kyoto, Japan's cultural heart and former imperial card-contentapital, preserves over 1,000 years of history. The city houses 17 UNESCO World Heritage sites, 
              including the golden Kinkaku-ji pavilion and the serene Ryoan-ji rock garden. Famous for its traditional arts, tea ceremonies, and geisha culture in the Gion 
              district, Kyoto offers visitors a glimpse into Japan's rich past. The city's seasonal beauty peaks during cherry blossom season and autumn foliage, drawing 
              millions of visitors to its temples, shrines, and traditional gardens.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>